            "body": "> * [x]  support `buf=0` to mean \"current buffer\"? `vim.pos(0)`, `:extmark(0,...)`, etc. [ref](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38665#discussion_r3040287364)\n\nSince we've made buffer a mandatory parameter, I think we can make buf=0 have this meaning and make it a default, which can satisfy those who don't need the buf key, and can also be functionally fault-tolerant.\n\n",
