            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The key to moving `vim.pos` out of its experimental stage should be whether we always use numeric indices instead of hash indices like `row` and `col`, and how much of a performance impact providing OOP operations (or `setmetatable`) for it would have.\n\nI performed some benchmarks on my local machine, but the results were inconsistent and difficult to explain. I will continue to look into this when I have time, but this won't block anyone else from working on it. Leaving a reminder here.",
