        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The benchmarks I conducted show that the performance improvement is limited; here is the [benchmark script](https://gist.github.com/ofseed/b309e2bfc1b2315fd3aeb1b2b8d022c8)\n\nThe result on LuaJIT is:\n```\ncount=1000000\ncreate numeric           0.054635 sec  54.635 ns/pos   checksum=999806126700\ncreate hash              0.074550 sec  74.550 ns/pos   checksum=999806126700\ncreate numeric object    0.054207 sec  54.207 ns/pos   checksum=999806126700\ncreate hash object       0.075953 sec  75.953 ns/pos   checksum=999806126700\nnumeric index [1]/[2]    0.005657 sec  2.829 ns/read  checksum=999806126700\nhash index row/col       0.007742 sec  3.871 ns/read  checksum=999806126700\nnumeric + metatable      0.006463 sec  3.232 ns/read  checksum=999806126700\nhash + metatable         0.009478 sec  4.739 ns/read  checksum=999806126700\n```\nThe result on PUC Lua 5.1 is:\n```\ncreate numeric           0.152979 sec  152.979 ns/pos   checksum=1000341133338\ncreate hash              0.193182 sec  193.182 ns/pos   checksum=1000341133338\ncreate numeric object    0.218988 sec  218.988 ns/pos   checksum=1000341133338\ncreate hash object       0.263173 sec  263.173 ns/pos   checksum=1000341133338\nnumeric index [1]/[2]    0.032412 sec  16.206 ns/read  checksum=1000341133338\nhash index row/col       0.030668 sec  15.334 ns/read  checksum=1000341133338\nnumeric + metatable      0.029530 sec  14.765 ns/read  checksum=1000341133338\nhash + metatable         0.028757 sec  14.379 ns/read  checksum=1000341133338\n```\nSince the indexing method here involves only simple addition, I am not yet certain if it represents real-world scenarios. I will conduct more detailed tests later, perhaps by directly comparing the current `vim.pos` and `vim.range` instead of writing new ones in the benchmark.\n\nHowever, if the performance gap is this small (<2x), it seems not worth making too many sacrifices to convenience for, as these operations are already fast enough to be measured in nanoseconds.",
